<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1732089-why-is-it-so-melodramatically-tragic">Why is it so melodramatically tragic?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1732089'><a id="like_count_community_question_1732089" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1732089?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F12083.Long_Day_s_Journey_into_Night">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1732089-why-is-it-so-melodramatically-tragic">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1732089-why-is-it-so-melodramatically-tragic">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/86363071-meursault-jacobson-lamberts"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1594683850i/86363071._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/86363071-meursault-jacobson-lamberts">Meursault Jacobson-Lamberts</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It isn&apos;t melodramatically tragic? It&apos;s tragic, yes, but there isn&apos;t much melodrama. What melodrama is there in this play? Also, asking the question &quot;w<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It isn't melodramatically tragic? It's tragic, yes, but there isn't much melodrama. What melodrama is there in this play? Also, asking the question "why" something happens in a work of literature, is completely unreasonable. It IS. WHY it is doesn't matter, in fact the real interrogative should be "how?" What a weird question to ask.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1026646" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1026646&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F1732089-why-is-it-so-melodramatically-tragic%2Fanswers%2F1026646-it-isn-t">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

